<TEXT>
the feature race at mehamas summer fest 
wasnt exactly a display of blazing speed but they didnt call it 
the slug and scotch broom festival for nothing 
humor helped make up for the lack of action in the race 
saturday in which the first of the critters to ooze its way out of 
a ring was declared winner 
he was going pretty fast wasnt he said daniel urquhart 
8 of aumsville whose slug crept to the championship 
rick urquhart father of the winning slug trainer said he found 
the racer at a state park 
we definitely searched high and low for this one we didnt 
take any backyard varieties he said well probably retire 
this one for the year maybe well catch the same one next year 
the festival the towns first in 30 years was the brainchild 
of businessmen mike boyles and bill mercer who came up with the 
idea over a drink at mercers fish hatchery tavern 
i was talking about how i was glad scotch broom season was 
over and he said something about how slugs oughta be banned and 
it just came together said boyles scotch broom is a bushlike 
weed with small yellow flowers that grows along roadways 
i guess we were kind of bored boyles said 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
at 14 feet tall and 30 feet long 
wilbir stands out from other peacocks 
of course its foliage not plumage that wilbir shows off and 
he cant strut around because hes a peat sculpture 
with 2000 begonias blooming on his chest head and tail he has 
drawn some surprised looks at michigan state universitys new 
horticulture demonstration gardens 
when i first saw it i thought it was a dinosaur said 
bobbie haskell who came for an evening walk in the gardens over 
the weekend 
we put in the peacock to get a little attention and show how 
spectacular its going to be said michigan state horticulture 
professor will carlson 
wilbir is short for wills bird after carlson who is in 
charge of the fiveyear project to construct the new garden 
it will be a worldclass garden it will probably be one of 
the finest in this country he said 
when finished in 1993 flowers will bloom over 7 acres and 
wilbir will be the centerpiece of the gardens circular entrance 
pavilion 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

