<TEXT>
benito ortiz a cuban who took up painting 
after retiring as a letter carrier and gained renown for his 
primitive scenes is dead at the age of 93 the cuban news agency 
prensa latina reported 
ortiz died saturday at his home in sancti spiritus a city in 
central cuba after a long illness that kept him away from his work 
for almost a decade the staterun news agency said monday 
the dispatch monitored in mexico city did not name the illness 
ortiz took up painting to escape from boredom he said when 
he retired after many years with the cuban postal service 
his colorful primitivist scenes of landscapes picturesque 
streets plazas and houses in his former hometown of trinidad 
started to gain him stature throughout latin america in the early 
1960s 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP890801-0003 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
a popular israeli singer of egyptian descent 
asked to entertain at an army generals goingaway party caused a 
minor scandal by singing a song about the 19monthold palestinian 
uprising 
the 20yearold singer haya samir appeared on nationwide 
television monday to defend herself after newspaper reports said 
her performance the previous night was met with boos and shouts 
from an audience that included defense minister yitzhak rabin 
the song she sang included such lines as those oppressed on 
the road prisoners of killing hungry for justice 
chewing their hatred mother earth is bleeding wounded by the 
war cursed by force and hatred 
samir who served in the army as a member of an entertainment 
troupe was invited because she was a favorite of maj gen yitzhak 
mordechai who was being honored with a party as he was transferred 
from head of the armys southern command to head of central command 
in the job he is leaving mordechai was responsible for putting 
down the uprising in the occupied gaza strip his new 
responsibility will be the west bank also torn by the revolt 
against israeli occupation 
the masscirculation daily maariv quoted one top officer as 
remarking after the show i am shocked yitzhak mordecai loved 
her singing and we wanted to give him a nice time she used us 
according to the paper samir said after the party i did not 
intend to sing a political song this is a song about life 
speaking on israel television monday she said the idea to sing 
the controversial song which she wrote herself came to her as she 
mounted the stage 
samir was born to egyptian moslem parents who immigrated to 
israel israeli newspapers said she was the only arab woman to ever 
serve in the army though some arab men regularly serve in the 
israeli military 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

