<TEXT>
before this weeks report that lt col 
william r higgins was hanged at least eight other foreign kidnap 
victims including two americans had been killed by their 
abductors in lebanon 
here is a brief review 
william buckley 57 the cia beirut station chief was 
kidnapped march 16 1984 the proiranian shiite group islamic 
jihad claimed oct 4 1985 it killed him but no body was found 
on jan 20 1987 vice president george bush confirmed that buckley 
had been killed a bachelor from medford mass buckley was 
assigned to the us embassy in beirut in 1983 
peter kilburn 62 of san francisco a librarian at the 
american university of beirut disappeared dec 3 1984 and was 
found shot to death with two british hostages april 17 1986 a 
nearby note said a group called arab revolutionary cells killed 
them in retaliation for the us air attack on libya two days 
earlier 
leigh douglas 34 a british professor at the american 
university of beirut disappeared march 28 1986 in west beirut 
he was found shot dead with kilburn 
philip padfield 40 a british language teacher disappeared at 
the same time as douglas he also was found dead with kilburn 
nicolas kluiters a dutch roman catholic priest disappeared in 
eastern lebanon march 14 1985 his body was found strangled in the 
area april 1 1985 
denis hill a briton who taught english at the american 
university of beirut failed to show up for work may 27 1985 and 
was found shot to death may 29 1985 
arkady katkov 32 a cultural attache at the soviet embassy in 
beirut was abducted sept 30 1985 with three other soviet 
diplomats and was found murdered oct 2 in a west beirut suburb 
the three other soviets were freed 
michel seurat a french academic researcher was kidnapped may 
22 1985 on march 5 1986 an islamic jihad statement claimed 
seurat 39 had been executed his wife later confirmed that 
french officials told her he was dead 
in addition the british foreign office says it also seeks word 
on alec collett a new yorkbased british journalist on assignment 
with a un relief agency who was kidnapped march 25 1985 in 
south lebanon his palestinian abductors claimed april 23 1986 
that they had killed him but his body was never found 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP890801-0006 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
here is a chronology of events in the holding of american kidnap 
victims in lebanon 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
feb 10 frank regier engineering professor at american 
university in beirut abducted near west beirut campus 
feb 26 us marines withdraw from beirut 
march 7 jeremy levin beirut chief for us cable news 
network kidnapped as walks to work in west beirut 
march 16 gunmen abduct us embassy political officer william 
buckley outside home in west beirut 
april 15 regier and kidnapped frenchman christian joubert gain 
freedom from unidentified captors shiite amal militia claims 
credit for rescue 
may 8 kidnappers overpower american presbyterian pastor 
benjamin weir on west beirut street and carry him off 
may 9 anonymous caller to french news agency claims islamic 
jihad shadowy antiwestern group of shiite moslems holds buckley 
levin weir 
sept 20 carbomb at us embassy annex in east beirut kills 
at least 14 people including two americans 
dec 3 american university librarian peter kilburn fails to 
report to work it is later claimed he was kidnapped by islamic 
jihad 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
jan 8 rev lawrence martin jenco roman catholic priest 
abducted from car by gunmen in beirut anonymous caller later says 
jenco and four other missing americans will be freed if all 
americans leave lebanon 
feb 14 levin gains freedom in lebanon and is turned over to 
us authorities by syria he says he escaped islamic jihad says 
it freed him 
march 16 terry anderson chief mideast correspondent of the 
associated press abducted on beirut street caller says islamic 
jihad kidnapped anderson 
may 16 islamic jihad warns of catastrophic consequences 
for hostages if kuwait does not free 17 islamic jihad comrades 
jailed in kuwait for december 1983 bombing of us and french 
embassies there 
may 28 gunmen kidnap david p jacobsen american director of 
american university hospital as he walks to work in west beirut 
may 30 caller claiming to represent islamic jihad says group 
killed denis hill british teacher of english at american 
university who disappeared may 27 and was later found shot in head 
and holds jacobsen 
june 10 gunmen on beirut airport highway kidnap american 
thomas sutherland acting agriculture dean at american university 
june 30 lebanese terrorists free last 39 hostages from twa 
jetliner they hijacked and forced to beirut 
sept 9 president reagan announces weir has been freed after 
16 months in captivity 
oct 4 islamic jihad claims it has killed buckley in 
retaliation for israeli air raid on plo headquarters in tunisia it 
later releases photographs it says show buckleys body and offers 
to turn body over to united nations if israel releases 100 
palestinian prisoners 
nov 8 in open letter four captive americans anderson 
jenco jacobsen and sutherland call on reagan to have mercy 
and negotiate with kidnappers 
nov 13 church of england official terry waite begins 
mediation to try to gain hostages release shuttling among beirut 
washington and european capitals 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
april 17 kilburn and two other hostages british educators 
leigh douglas and philip padfield found shot to death east of 
beirut note says arab revolutionary cells killed them in 
retaliation for april 15 us air attack on libya 
april 23 revolutionary organization of socialist moslems says 
it has killed kidnapped british journalist alec collett in 
retaliation for british complicity in us attack on libya 
videotape purporting to show him hanged is made public collett on 
assignment with un relief agency was kidnapped march 25 1985 
july 26 jenco freed he later delivers confidential message to 
reagan from kidnappers 
sept 9 american educator frank herbert reed kidnapped in west 
beirut 
sept 12 american university accountant joseph cicippio 
abducted on west beirut campus callers claim responsibility for 
both reed and cicippio abductions in name of two groups 
resurrection cells and arab revolutionary cellsomar moukhtar 
forces later revolutionary justice organization claims 
responsibility for kidnapping of cicippio 
oct 21 revolutionary justice organization claims to have 
kidnapped another american in beirut writer edward austin tracy 
nov 2 jacobsen is released in beirut islamic jihad says us 
must continue pursuing current approaches to win freedom for 
other hostages 
nov 3 first reports surface that us beginning in 1985 
arranged arms shipments to iran in exchange for hostage releases 
nov 28 irans parliament speaker hashemi rafsanjani says 
tehran government will help free hostages if washington returns 
frozen iranian assets in us talks on returning frozen us assets 
to iran are later suspended 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
jan 20 vice president george bush says hostage buckley died 
after torture anglican church mediator waite drops from sight in 
beirut unconfirmed reports say he is captive of extremists 
jan 24 three americans jesse jonathan turner alann steen 
and robert polhill and indian mithileshwar singh all faculty 
members of beirut university college are kidnapped from the 
campus group calling itself islamic jihad for liberation of 
palestine claims responsibility 
feb 9 islamic jihad for liberation of palestine threatening 
to kill turner steen polhill and singh unless israel frees arab 
prisoners postpones the act just before deadline 
march 26 videotape released in which turner says fellow 
hostage steen is ill and dying and urging release of arab 
prisoners in israel in exchange for hostages freedom 
june 17 american journalist charles glass on leave from his 
job at abc news is kidnapped in west beirut he escapes two months 
later 
dec 24 kidnappers issue videotape of anderson in which he 
appeals to president reagan to win the hostages release saying 
there is a limit for how long we can last 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
feb 17 us marine lt col william r higgins chief of 
observer unit attached to un peacekeeping force in lebanon is 
seized by gunmen on southern lebanese highway the organization of 
oppressed on earth claims to hold him and demands release of 
prisoners held by israel 
may 4 the last three french hostages in lebanon are set free 
they say a fourth french hostage michel seurat died in captivity 
french premier michel rocard later says france will reestablish 
diplomatic relations with iran 
oct 3 indian professor mithileshwar singh is freed 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
march 3 lebanons most influential shiite moslem cleric sheik 
mohammed hussein fadlallah says the foreign hostages should be 
freed because abduction is wrong 
june 8 irans parliament speaker hashemi rafsanjani says 
iran will help free american hostages in lebanon if the united 
states tries to win freedom for iranians held by christian forces 
in lebanon 
july 28 israeli commandos abduct sheik abdul karim obeid a 
shiite moslem cleric and a leader of the hezbollah from his home 
in south lebanon 
july 30 organization of the oppressed on earth threatens to 
kill higgins if obeid is not freed 
july 31 organization of the oppressed on earth says higgins 
has been killed releases videotape purporting to show his hanged 
body revolutionary justice organization threatens to kill cicippio 
if shiite cleric is not freed 
</TEXT>
