<TEXT>
country singer charlie daniels says many 
working people have had their fill with the state of the nation 
people in this country are fed up daniels said during a 
weekend concert appearance at dodge city i know because i talk 
to people im on the road all the time im talking to the people 
out there 
theyre sick and tired of child abuse theyre sick and tired 
of drugs theyre sick and tired of murders theyre sick sick 
sick of it 
his bands appearance included the first concert performance of 
a new song simple man title track from an upcoming album 
we appeal to the blue collar people out there daniels said 
theyre the ones who make this country run i think i can play 
for them because i am a working man i come from a long line of 
farmers and timbermen thats where my heart is with those people 
who get up in the morning and go to work 
at 52 daniels says he feels more creative than ever 
i thank god every day of my life that i enjoy the business im 
in so much he said im going to keep doing this as long as i 
can 
