building but still strong in factory construction which is 
supported by manufacturers success in selling more goods overseas 
the one thing that is restraining additional investment in the 
industrial sector is that everyone is looking over their shoulder 
to see if theres a recession coming he said the people in 
charge of investment are trying to be very cautious because they 
realize were going to get a rude surprise sooner or later 
he predicted a small increase in construction activity in the 
second half of this year but not enough to get excited about 
