alleged conspiracy citing his fifth amendment right against 
selfincrimination and other constitutional rights 
the matter now goes to the full senate and if approved from 
there to a court that would be asked to force borders to testify or 
be held in civil contempt and jailed 
under questioning from anderson hastings offered an explanation 
for one of the key points being used against him on sept 16 
1981 he appeared for dinner at 8 pm in the dining room of the 
fontainebleau hotel in miami 
a few days earlier borders had promised to produce hastings in 
the dining room at that time on that date the idea was to prove he 
could influence the judge and thus encourage a payoff from a man he 
believed to be a defendant trying to buy his way out of a 
threeyear racketeering sentence 
actually he made the remark to an fbi undercover agent wearing 
a hidden tape recorder 
hastings testified he went to the fontainebleu that night with a 
date because borders had suggested that he would meet him there at 
the time borders was in las vegas for a prizefight between sugar 
ray leonard and thomas hearns hastings said the failure of borders 
to materialize was not that unusual and that it did not surprise 
him 
throughout the case hastings has maintained that borders a 
longtime friend and law school classmate was a rainmaker who 
boasted of influence he did not actually have as a means of 
drumming up clients 
hastings also offered an explanation for behavior that 
prosecutors say suggests an effort to elude the fbi on oct 9 
1981 the day that borders was arrested as he drove out of a 
suburban virginia motel with a garment bag stuffed with cash and 
undercover agent h paul rico by his side 
at the time hastings was in the lenfant plaza hotel in 
washington preparing for a testimonial dinner in honor of borders 
then a leader in the national bar association and according to a 
house report and several witnesses a figure who wielded influence 
at the white house in the late 1970s 
told of the borders arrest hastings swiftly left for florida 
and went miles out of his way to baltimorewashington international 
airport to catch a plane when washingtons ntional airport was only 
minutes away 
i went there to get a flight that i thought would get me to 
fort lauderdale hastings testified i really expected to 
see the fbi at the national airport the baltimore airport or fort 
lauderdale 
