southeast texas was hit with a deluge of rain 8 inches at one 
spot from the remnants of hurricane chantal and thunderstorms 
swept through the lower mississippi valley to the southern atlantic 
coast on tuesday 
chantal hit southeast texas on tuesday morning and weakened to a 
tropical storm at 3 pm edt the center of the storm was 25 miles 
north of houston and moving northwest at 12 mph 
maximum sustained winds decreased to 55 mph with higher gusts 
in squalls mainly over the gulf of mexico to the south of the 
center the storm was expected to weaken as it moved further inland 
in addition to strong winds torrential rains were reported 
across southeast texas more than 7 inches of rain fell at 
friendswood and houston tuesday morning with 4 inches dumped in 
one hour clear lake city was drenched by 8 inches of rain while 
galveston received 6 inches 
