<TEXT>
japanese gangsters raked in more than 93 billion 
last year in a mix of legal and illegal businesses the national 
police agency said in a report released tuesday 
it estimated that japans gangsters made about 32 billion just 
from sales of illegal drugs 
gambling blackmarketeering protection rackets and extortion 
were also listed as major operations 
income from construction real estate financing and other legal 
activities also contributed to the haul the report said 
the 1988 estimate was nearly 22 billion higher than in 1978 
the most recent year available for comparison said an npa 
official who spoke on condition of anonymity 
the agency reports annually on gang activity but estimates gang 
income only every 10 years 
the report said the 86552 known gangsters as of the end of last 
year belonged to 3197 gangs across the nation the figures were 
roughly equal to those of 1987 
police say they can reliably estimate gang membership because of 
the japanese underworlds high profile it is not uncommon for a 
gang to operate from a wellmarked office or to make a list of its 
members available to police or the media 
the report said that while the number of gangsters seems to have 
leveled off over the past few years syndicates are showing a 
continued trend of consolidation increasing their strength by 
forming alliances over a wide area 
nearly 40 percent of all japanese gangsters commonly known as 
yakuza belong to the nations three largest syndicates the 
yamaguchigumi inagawakai and sumiyoshi rengokai which have 
branches covering most of the country 
though their operations are primarily domestic japanese gangs 
smuggle in drugs and guns from abroad and are believed to be 
setting up bases and operating overseas the report said it did 
not specify where but police have acknowledged yakuza activities 
in the philippines taiwan thailand and hong kong and also guam 
and hawaii 
yakuza find their expansion abroad hindered by the lack of large 
japanesespeaking communities police say 
the report said an increasing number of foreign gangs are 
operating in japan often with the consent of the domestic 
underworld it singled out taiwanese gangsters known to be an 
important source of stimulant drugs mostly methamphetamines 
</TEXT>
