<TEXT>
mission controllers ordered voyager 2 to 
increase velocity and change direction slightly tuesday as the 
spacecraft began to come under the influence of the gravity tug of 
neptune some 21 million miles away 
data that voyager sent more than 27 billion miles back to earth 
confirmed the start of a command sequence to begin a 7minute 
firing of its thrusters said a statement from jet propulsion 
laboratory 
the firing had actually begun four hours and two minutes 
earlier the time it took the radio signal to reach earth from the 
distant craft 
confirmation of the maneuvers success was not expected until 
review of spacecraft telemetry later in the day 
the maneuver was to boost voyagers speed by 21 mph and nudge 
the oneton spacecraft slightly sideways jpl said voyager was 
traveling at 42187 mph 
two more corrections are planned to put voyager on a course to 
pass just 3000 miles above neptunes northern polar region on aug 
24 
flight engineers also reported that data shows neptunes 
gravitational attraction has slightly but detectably accelerated 
voyager 
the point at which the planets gravity began to have an effect 
is hard to pinpoint said lanny miller manager of the voyager 
flight engineering office 
voyager is always under the influence of the planets gravity 
but you dont see it in the data until youre real close miller 
said 
the spacecrafts cameras have thus far been observing the entire 
neptunian system but on saturday will begin observing specific 
points such as a large dark spot and smaller spots in the 
atmosphere 
the search for moons and ring arcs will also continue neptune 
was known to have only two moons until voyager 2 found a third moon 
last month 
voyager 2 was launched from florida in 1977 and flew past 
jupiter in 1979 saturn in 1981 and uranus in 1986 
jpl controls americas unmanned planetary exploration program 
for the national aeronautics and space administration 
