japans seasonally adjusted unemployment rate in 
june fell to 22 percent the lowest level in seven years the 
government announced tuesday 
the statistics bureau of the prime ministers office said the 
number of jobholders grew by 133 million from a year earlier the 
largest gain in more than 15 years it brought the total number of 
employed to 6239 million 
it said there were 134 million japanese without work in the 
month a decrease of 100000 from a year earlier 
in may the unemployment rate was 24 percent 
japans economy has continued to expand robustly and rising 
domestic demand has spurred many manufacturers to boost production 
figures released by the labor ministry on tuesday indicated 
there were 134 job offers for every 100 people looking for work 
japans jobless rate would be higher if it were calculated by 
us or european methods 
in japan members of the armed forces and people working more 
than one hour in the last week of the month when data are 
tabulated are counted as employed in the united states military 
personnel traditionally are not considered part of the labor force 
and those working less than 15 hours a week are considered 
unemployed 
japan has used its current method to calculate unemployment 
since 1953 
