a slight earthquake rattled the portland 
area tuesday afternoon but there were no reports of property 
damage or injury 
the temblor measured 39 on the richter scale and was centered 
10 miles below the lacamas lake area just northeast of camas 
wash said chris jonientztrisler seismic analyst at the 
university of washington seismology lab 
the quake reported at 425 pm was on the borderline between 
minor and moderate jonientztrisler said she also said there was 
one small aftershock but she had no details on its size 
officers with the portland police bureau and clark county 
sheriffs department said people called to report the earthquake 
but there were no reports of damage 
it was like a sudden jolt like somebody backed into the 
building said bill wade who lives near portland state 
university 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake a quake of magnitude 35 can cause slight damage and 
one of magnitude 4 can cause moderate damage an earthquake 
measuring 5 can cause considerable damage 
