percent in may that means that a family earning the national 
median of 32760 a year had 993 percent of the funds needed to 
qualify for conventional financing covering 80 percent of the 
purchase price of a home costing a median price of 93200 
the decline in affordability in june was blamed on an increase 
in mortgage rates and a 600 increase in the median resale price of 
a home mortgage rates at closing climbed to 1059 percent in june 
up from a nationwide average of 1046 percent in may the 
association uses a composite rate reflecting both fixedrate and 
adjustablerate mortgages 
