<TEXT>
boise cascade corp has unveiled a plan to 
install one of the worlds largest paper machines at its mill in 
this androscoggin river town a 450 million project that will 
continue the mills twodecade trend toward a smaller work force 
the new machine with an annual capacity of 318000 tons will 
be the centerpiece of a 770 million modernization program designed 
to turn one of the nations oldest pulp and paper mills into one of 
the largest and most productive manufacturers of coated papers for 
catalogs and magazines the boise idahobased company said monday 
coated paper from the mill in western maine is used in such 
publications as time national geographic people and vanity fair 
as well as such catalogs as ll bean horchow and macys baxter 
said 
the company said it expects to begin installing the machine and 
building related facilities in 1991 with a startup of production 
planned for late 1993 
the new machine will lead to an unspecified reduction in the 
1600member work force at the rumford mill according to eric s 
baxter spokesman at the offices of boise cascades coated paper 
division in portland 
well be shutting down four very old machines to make way for 
the new machine said baxter he said there will be no layoffs 
and all job losses will be carried out through attrition 
the president of local 900 of the united paperworkers 
international union which represents some 1250 production workers 
at boise cascade declined comment on the merits of the project but 
expressed surprise that it was announced at this time 
they management told us about a month ago that it was being 
put on hold for at least nine months to a year before it was going 
to be announced now they go ahead and announce it don barker 
said 
barker whose union was involved in a violent strike at boise 
cascade three years ago noted that the mill had more than 3000 
workers before automation began to shrink the number of jobs 
built around the turn of the century at a bend in the 
androscoggin river the mill has produced both coated and uncoated 
papers when the new machine is installed production will rise to 
753000 tons a year and be made up entirely of coated papers the 
company said 
the project hinges on obtaining state and federal environmental 
permits to install and operate the machine 
