us bankruptcy judge harold abramson said 
creditors in the bankruptcy case of william herbert and nancy hunt 
can submit suggestions on how the hunts should repay their debts 
the judges decision monday shifts leverage in the case from the 
debtors to the creditors creditors previously had to base 
negotiations on a plan developed by herbert hunt 
abramson said he will allow the suggestions because he did not 
see a resolution coming from herbert hunts proposed settlement 
i find that the mere filing of competing plans will not impede 
debtors negotiations said the judge who ultimately will decide 
how creditors are paid 
the internal revenue service and manufacturers hanover trust co 
of new york two of the largest creditors in the herbert hunt 
bankruptcy said they will file a repayment plan by friday 
this is exactly what we have been asking for said grover 
hartt iii an attorney for the irs 
the irs claims herbert hunt owes about 300 million in back 
taxes while brother nelson bunker hunt owes 700 million the irs 
has agreed to settle both cases for about 350 million 
bunker and herbert owned onethird of the worlds supply of 
silver bullion from a silvershopping spree that began in 1973 
government attorneys claim 
as the price tumbled to 10 an ounce from 50 an ounce the 
brothers found themselves with debts totaling as much as 2 billion 
and creditors threatening the familys beloved placid oil co 
barbara houser attorney for the peruvian silver mining company 
minpeco sa which seeks 251 million said she also has a plan 
prepared 
abramson gave bunker hunt and his wife caroline until aug 31 
to work out a repayment plan with their creditors 
the judge said the hunt cases are two of the most difficult 
chapter 11 cases a lawyer could envision 
stephen a mccartin attorney for herbert and nancy hunt said 
that allowing creditors to submit repayment proposals will make 
it more difficult to reach a consensual plan 
the irs plan to be filed this week in the herbert hunt case will 
recommend that the agency receive 70 percent of a liquidating 
trust or about 60 million under the plan the irs also would get 
90 million in a nondischargeable claim that would be paid after 
herbert emerges from bankruptcy 
the irs is negotiating a similar settlement proposal with bunker 
and his wife caroline 
the hunt brothers including lamar hunt are in us tax court 
contesting the millions of dollars in taxes the irs says it is owed 
from the 1982 dissolution of a partnership set up to repay their 
debts after the silver price collapse 
the hunts nonjury tax trial reconvenes in washington dc 
on aug 21 
