of simmonscontrolled concerns headed by valhi corp stated they 
now hold more than 6 million shares or 946 percent of lockheeds 
common stock 
thats an increase from an 803 percent stake reported july 17 
by simmons one of lockheeds largest individual shareholders 
the latest sec filing did not state why simmons had increased 
his holdings indicating the reason had not changed since a june 12 
filing 
in that filing when he acquired 625 percent of lockheed 
simmons said he was buying the defense contractors shares for 
purposes of investment and in order to acquire a significant equity 
interest in the company 
equity is the ownership interest shareholders possess in a 
corporation 
in the june filing simmons denied having immediate plans to 
take over the company by stock ownership or other means although 
he didnt discount such a move in the future 
earlier this year simmons a dallas billionaire with holdings 
in the chemical timber and sugar industries revealed he had a 53 
percent stake in lockheed the calabasas califbased maker of the 
stealth jet fighter 
that disclosure prompted lockheed to create an employee stock 
ownership plan esop that in effect blocked any takeover attempt 
under delaware law lockheed is incorporated in delaware 
the day after lockheed created the esop simmons whose worth is 
estimated by fortune magazine at 15 billion reduced his holdings 
from 53 percent to 42 percent 
according to the latest sec filing valhi inc controls 34 
million or 549 percent of lockheed valhi also controls nl 
industries inc which holds 129 million lockheed shares or 204 
percent and nl chemicals which holds 122 million or 193 
percent 
nl industries and nl chemicals have purchased more than 909000 
lockheed shares since july 17 for between 4750 and 49 according 
to the sec filing 
